nterspersed references to writers such as Goethe, Rilke, Kafka, Freud, and Benjamin, Blumenberg gathers evidence to raise the singular question that, in his view, Christian theology has not been able to answer: How can an omnipotent God be so offended by his creatures that he must sacrifice and abandon his own Son?  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aMusicxSocial aspectszGermany. 0aMusiczGermanyy19th centuryxHistory and criticism. 4aMusical Arts & Ethnomusicology. 4aReligious Studies. 7aRELIGION / Philosophy.2bisacsh  abach and philosophy, Gnosticism and christianity, music and religion, Kierkegaard, Nietzsche, Kafka.1 aFleming, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMüller-Sievers, Helmut, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021z978311073908408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishz978311075400108iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021z9783110753776oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2021 Englishz978311075419308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2021z9783110753974oZDB-23-DGF40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781501759079?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781501759079423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781501759079/original  a978-3-11-073908-4  Cornell University Press Complete eBook-Package 2021b2021  a978-3-11-075400-1  EBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2021 Englishb2021  a978-3-11-075419-3  EBOOK PACKAGE Theol., Relig.Stud., Jewish Stud. 2021 Englishb2021  aEBA_EMB  aGBV-deGruyter-alles